The paper presents a novel deep learning model for collective classification in multi-relational domains. The model has many desirable theoretical properties and is evaluated on multiple real-world applications. Given the focus on deep learning and classification, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
